quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,"O you who believe, shall I tell you about a trade that saves you from a painful punishment"
  61,11,"That you believe in Allah and His Messenger, and carry out Jihad in His way with your riches and your lives. That is much better for you, if you but know"
  61,12,"(If you do this,) He will forgive your sins, and will admit you to gardens beneath which rivers flow, and to pleasant dwellings in gardens of eternity. That is the great achievement"
  61,13,"And (He will give you) another thing, which you love: Help from Allah, and victory, near at hand"
  61,14,"O you who believe, be supporters of (the religion of) Allah, just as ‘Isa, son of Maryam, said to the Disciples, .Who are my supporters towards Allah?. The Disciples said, .We are the supporters of (the religion of) Allah. So a group from the children of Isra‘il believed, and another group disbelieved. Then We supported those who believed against their enemy, and they became victors"